      "side": 1,
      "message": "We need to escape this for shell. Otherwise it may allow unexpected shell injection, e.g. export HTTP_PROXY\u003d\"foo cat /etc/passwd;\"\n\n var envVarName \u003d regexp.Compile(\"^[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*$\")\n\n for _, env :\u003d range envVars {\n   parts :\u003d strings.SplitN(env, \"\u003d\", 2)\n   if len(parts) !\u003d 2 {\n     return nil, errors.New(\"invalid environment variable definition\")\n   }\n   if !envVarName.MatchString(parts[0]) {\n     return nil, errors.New(\"invalid environment variable name\")\n   }\n   envPrefix +\u003d fmt.Sprintf(\"%s\u003d%s \", parts[0], testexec.EscapeString(parts[1]))\n }\n\nAbout the allowed character set in environment variable names, I found this article is useful: https://stackoverflow.com/a/2821183",
